        "client_msg_id": "a38ac3fe-760b-4c52-9bcd-f8ad14ac83f0",
        "text": "Some thoughts about <https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=_dhsm0PLOk0|The Computing Historian Recovering Ideas We Threw Away>\n\n• we finally have asynchronous multi-tasking - i.e. the internet - many independent computers, running at their own speed\n• we have some of the same “concurrency” issues, with internet, yet simpler, since internet does not allow actual memory sharing (you can share data, but not memory)\n• modern computing has been overrun by technical\/academic complication, not by UX simplicity\n• the “new” invention of CompSci is _not_ “programming” but “re-programming”\n• Design Recovery to lift designs out of old software and to re-express them in code for new RMs - what is the meta-language? (factbases of triples?)\n<https:\/\/programmingsimplicity.substack.com\/p\/some-thoughts-about-the-computing?r=1egdky|...>",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
